==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Metacetone
<hw>Me*tac"e*tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>met-</ets> + <ets>acetone</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
colorless liquid of an agreeable odor, <chform>C6H10O</chform>, obtained
by distilling a mixture of sugar and lime; -- so called because formerly
regarded as a polymeric modification of acetone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metachloral</ent>⟦br⟧
